{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Coffee Pecan Cake","content":["Preheat oven to 170°C and line a cake tin (approx. 35 cm x 25 cm x 6 cm) with baking paper.","In a small bowl, dissolve coffee in boiling water and set aside to cool slightly.","Place pecans in mixing bowl and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place butter and sugar in mixing bowl then cream <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add flour, eggs and baking powder then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add 2 Tbsp reserved coffee mixture, vanilla and reserved chopped pecans then, with aid of spatula, mix <b>10-20 sec\/\/speed 4.5<b>, until combined.","Transfer mixture to prepared tin then bake for 15-20 minutes (170°C) until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. Leave sponge in tin to cool for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make buttercream."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["Place butter, sugar, milk, vanilla and remaining 2 Tbsp coffee mixture in mixing bowl then cream <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then cream again <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a large piping bag fitted with a 10 mm star-shaped nozzle.","Using a long, serrated knife, level off the top of the cake to make a flat surface. Carefully slice the cake in half horizontally to make two layers, leaving the top layer in place.","Using a cookie cutter (Ø 5 cm), cut 18 rounds from the double-layered cake to make 36 in total (see tip). Pipe approx. 1 Tbsp icing onto each cake round and layer into 3 to make 12 (3-layered) cakes. Arrange 1 pecan half on top of each cake to finish. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Coffee Pecan Cake","content":["4 Tbsp instant coffee granules","4 Tbsp water, boiling","100 g pecan nuts","250 g unsalted butter, soft","275 g golden caster sugar","300 g self-raising flour","5 medium eggs","2 tsp baking powder","1 Tbsp vanilla extract"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["250 g unsalted butter, soft","500 g icing sugar","1 ½ Tbsp milk","2 tsp vanilla extract","12 pecan nut halves"]}],"id":"r364970","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-2c_EdZMj9Kw\/XZWpqFeoPwI\/AAAAAAAAfNI\/p9EnRzmcdAEAWpGicyI6pW2gcik4ZpnmQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1N-fo0S5ssNhtQHb.png","title":"Mini Coffee Pecan Layer Cakes","publishedAt":"2018-08-13T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6 g","fat":"39 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"75 g","calories":"2846 kJ \/ 681 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, wire rack, cookie cutter (Ø 5 cm), serrated knife, piping bag with star-shaped nozzle, skewer, cake tin (35 cm x 25 cm x 6 cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Don't throw away the leftover sponge pieces; they are great for making cake pops."],"basicInfo":["medium","55m","55m","12 pieces"]}